SIMPLE: unteach
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unteach
<hw>Un*teach"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>teach</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To cause to forget, or to lose from memory, or to
disbelieve what has been taught.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Experience will <qex>unteach</qex> us.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T.
Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One breast laid open were a school⟦br⟧
Which would <qex>unteach</qex> mankind the lust to shine or rule.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To cause to be forgotten; <as>as, to
<ex>unteach</ex> what has been learned</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unteam</ent>⟦br⟧
